# HookSniff AI Context

## Project Overview
HookSniff is a webhook infrastructure platform built in Rust (API) + Next.js (Dashboard).

## Architecture
- **API (Rust)**: GCP Cloud Run at `europe-west1` — `hooksniff-api-e6ztf3x2ma-ew.a.run.app`
- **Dashboard (Next.js 16)**: Vercel — `hooksniff.vercel.app`
- **Database**: Neon (PostgreSQL)
- **Redis**: Upstash
- **Monitoring**: Sentry + Grafana Cloud + Prometheus

## Email Setup (Updated 2026-06-09)
- **Provider priority**: Gmail SMTP → Resend → GCloud Gmail API → None
- **Active provider**: Gmail SMTP via `servetarslan02@gmail.com` + App Password
- **GCP Secrets**: `hooksniff-gmail-address`, `hooksniff-gmail-app-password`
- **Env vars**: `GMAIL_ADDRESS`, `GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD`

## Deployment
- GCP Project: `project-0d7b3b3f-2204-4957-909` (My First Project)
- GCP Cloud Build (`cloudbuild.yaml`) builds & deploys API + Worker
- Vercel auto-deploys dashboard from GitHub
- Secrets managed in GCP Secret Manager

## Key Files
- `api/src/email.rs` — Email provider routing (Resend/GmailSmtp/GCloud)
- `api/src/gmail_smtp.rs` — Gmail SMTP client (lettre)
- `api/src/resend_email.rs` — Resend client (fallback)
- `dashboard/src/lib/email.ts` — Dashboard-side email (Gmail API via GCP SA)
- `cloudbuild.yaml` — Main CI/CD pipeline
- `cloudbuild-run.yaml` — Alternate Cloud Run deploy

## Known Issues / Notes
- Resend requires custom domain — not configured, falls back to Gmail SMTP
- GCP Service Account (`GCP_SA_JSON`) not set up — not needed if Gmail SMTP works
- Dashboard email.ts uses Gmail API directly (separate from API email)

